Clinical implications of interleukin-18 levels in pediatric patients with Mycoplasma pneumoniae pneumonia. The immunological pathogenesis of Mycoplasma pneumoniae pneumonia is known to involve several cytokines. The serum levels of interleukin-18 (IL-18) were examined using enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay in 23 pediatric patients (median age 6 years range 4-13 years